This paper investigates the effect of network width on stochastic gradient descent and generalization in machine learning models. The study involves hyper-parameter search and analysis of MLPs, ConvNets, and ResNets, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
